Billy Mitchell was born with Apert syndrome, a rare genetic condition which causes malformations of the skull, face, hands and feet . 
  He underwent a series of major operations to correct the deformities . 
  He had a procedure to crack open and reshape his skull and another to rebuild his features . 
  He also had a titanium frame drilled into his head to relieve pressure on his brain . 
  Billy has undergone more than 50 operations to have his face rebuilt . 
 